Virgo Filament Survey

Probing the nearest cosmic web to reveal how galaxies thrive—or fade

The Virgo Filament Survey investigates how the filamentary environment influences the gas reservoirs and star formation activity of galaxies. To date, we have measured the molecular and atomic gas content of 220 galaxies embedded in the filaments surrounding the Virgo Cluster—the nearest galaxy cluster to us. Ongoing surveys are expanding this view by mapping star formation alongside the molecular and atomic gas, providing new insight into how large-scale structures drive galaxy evolution.
